metadata.name: Swedish Forest #42
metadata.description:
If I had to choose a place where time was frozen and where I could contemplate the landscape for eternity this place would be a scandinavian forest.
I have been contemplating these kind of landscape for a very long time both in Sweden and in the Pyrenees where the ecosystem is very similar.
This project generates an illustration of a scandinavian forest in many different situations. At day and at night, in every season of the year, next to a lake or not, with steep hills or at the plains, snowing, with preponderance of some plant species over others, etc.
The artwork is also drawn in various paint modes and layouts.

The sun or the moon may be visible, the moon shows always the actual moon phase based on the current date.
The reflection on the lake is the fxhash morse endcoded.


Developed in vanilla js using svg and canvas
Rendering can be unresponsive on slow devices
Click or touch to switch to Parallax mode, just move the mouse or finger.


[S] Download in SVG format
[D] Download in PNG format

Features:

Layout: Landscape, Portrait, Square
PredominantSpecies: Blueberry, Lingonberry, Calluna, Rocks, None
Trees: Mixed, PinesAndFirs, Birches, None
Season: Spring, Summer, Fall, Winter
DayNight: Day, Night
PaintStyle: Normal, Stroke, Paint, WhiteOnBlack, BlackOnWhite
ColorStyle: Normal, Crazy
HasLake: True, False
HasTrees: None, Few, Many, Crowded

metadata.description:

metadata.name: √∞olmen #77
metadata.description:
√∞olmen is a generative art project by Diego Pintos.
It draws rectangles with points instead a plain color or border. With some variations in the distribution of this points, we get a kind of noise depth effect.

12 carefully selected palettes. Based in Art Masterpieces and in Nature.
¬∑ Gioconda (Leonardo da Vinci)
¬∑ Guernika (Pablo Picasso)
¬∑ Nighthawks (Edward Hopper)
¬∑ Meninas (Diego Velazquez)
¬∑ Judith beheading Holofernes (Caravaggio)
¬∑ Al Siq (nature)
¬∑ guacamayo (nature)
¬∑ Salamanca (nature)
¬∑ mostaza (nature)
¬∑ Timanfaya (nature)
¬∑ piedra (nature)
¬∑ firefall (nature)

√∞olmen builds 10 compositions:
¬∑ Square
¬∑ PersonChen's Style
¬∑ Equilibrium
¬∑ Hanging
¬∑ Pyramid
¬∑ Row
¬∑ Column
¬∑ 3 columns (randomly aligned)
¬∑ 3 rows (randomly aligned)
¬∑ Frame

Density
¬∑ Tiny: Less than 35 rects. Rare
¬∑ Small: Less than 100 rects. Common.
¬∑ Medium: Less than 250 rects. Common.
¬∑ High: Less than 350 rects. Common.
¬∑ Massive: Less than 500 rects. Rare.
¬∑ Ultra: More than 500 rects. Rarest.

Rarities
¬∑ Rectangle filling type: Filled (95%) or unfilled (5%)
¬∑ Monochrome: Just black and white. Always unfilled. (1%)
¬∑ Dark mode: Dark background (20%). Dark mode can be monochrome.
¬∑ Habitable (90%). See humans later.

Humans
√∞olmen can host tiny humans. Contains a little code that draws humans looking down, in order to to provide size perspective.

Minting
Each √∞olmen contains all rarities inside. As a √∞olmen collector, you can display your final piece in all available formats, and rarity owners can display the regular filled composition. In addition, this can help if you want to print one or more formats.

Tricks and Keys
√∞olmen is responsive, you can zoom out your browser window and refresh to get a larger output.
's' save the current canvas
'd' toggle dark mode
'f' toggle fill mode
'm' toggle monochrome

More info and visual description:
https://thelirios.com/dolmen/

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Asterium #218
metadata.description:
Asterium is a token that will grow with you, for an entire year. Changing and morphing over time to eventually reach its equilibrium.

It is a token where I try to symbolize the journey of life.
Where looking back is the best way to look forward.
Where looking into the future is not a possibility.
Where each day is as uncertain as the next.

A token that will surprise you and have its ups and downs as it grows over time.



Pricing:
Dutch auction 64-16-8, where anybody that picks one up at 64 tez gets a print of how their galaxy looks on any day from the present to day 0. Meaning you can claim the print at any point in the future.

The print will be printed on high quality hahnem√ºhle torchon paper at 30x40 cm (11.81 x 15.75 in). Printed at a local print shop here in Utrecht. This paper has a rough texture to it that matches the textures of space perfectly.



Usage:
- Hover over your Asterium to view the name, date, days passed, status and render stats.
- Double press to export the current frame as a .png image.
- Use the slider at the bottom to scroll back in time to the days before today, you can go as far back as day 0 and as far forwards as today.
- The token refreshes every hour, so framing it in a digital picture frame is totally possible!

metadata.name: ARAUCO #92
metadata.description:
The Araucaria Araucana, also known as pew√©n, is a sacred tree for the Mapuche and an emblem of Chile. With an origin dating back 260 million years to the Triassic period, it is part of the oldest forests on the planet. These ancient trees are endangered due to logging, forest fires, and grazing.

ARAUCO is a tribute to araucarias and Mapuche iconography. Incorporating elements such as the Kultrung, the W√ºnelfe star, and the staggered cross Ng√ºmin, the work displays a typical landscape of southern Chile with the Andes Mountains in the background and the native forest. 

‚Äì

Press 's' to export a 4960x7016 PNG file suitable for A2 printing at 300 dpi.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Alleles #57
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.

attributes.name: Genetic Profile
attributes.value: Exploration of the information extracted from the provided genetic information suggests subject may experience intermittent episodes of disassociation and a thirst for power, yet also shows signs of superior interpersonal communication and persistence. Maximum potential hereditary height (excluding nutritional and environmental factors) is estimated at 210-217cm. Projected natural lifespan estimated at 83-91 years. Mutation present requires intermittent observation to determine existence of any latent abilities. Careful examination of markers 8 through 179, as these may indicate the presence of telekinesis and or synaptic entanglement (telepathic) abilities.

metadata.name: Annum #1809
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.
